Affiliation: The University of Michigan,  
Abstract: A new MHD code has been developed for massively parallel computers using adaptive mesh reflnement (AMR) and a new 8-wave Riemann solver. The code was implemented on a Cray T3D massively parallel computer with 512 PEs. In the flrst application, which modeled the expansion of the solar wind from the solar surface, the code achieved 13 GFLOPS. 
